<main class="container mb-3">
    <h1>Memberships</h1>
    <div>      
        <a id="subs"></a>
        <div class="row d-md-flex flex-md-row-reverse">
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 p-2">
                <img class="rounded-circle" src="/images/scifi.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-8 p-2">
                <h2>Sci-Fi Subscription</h2>
                <p>
                    €120 per year
                    <br>
                    Bold ideas. Visionary authors. Collector-grade editions.
                    <br>
                    The Science Fiction Subscription focuses on standout speculative fiction, from space opera and hard SF to genre-defining modern classics. Each edition is designed to be both a reading copy and a long-term collectible. These editions are designed to balance literary significance with collectability, making them suitable for both reading and display. Print runs are kept intentionally limited to preserve long-term value.
                </p> 
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="d-md-flex flex-md-row">
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-4 p-2">
                <img class="rounded-circle" src="/images/fantasy.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-12 col-md-6 col-lg-8 p-2">
                <h2>Fantasy Subscription</h2>
                <p>
                    €120 per year
                    <br>
                    Epic fantasy, crafted as collectible editions.  
                    <br>
                    The Fantasy Subscription is designed for readers who want more than a standard hardback. Each year, subscribers receive a carefully curated selection of exclusive fantasy titles produced as limited-run special editions. Every book is chosen for its long-term appeal, worldbuilding, and place within the modern fantasy canon. These editions are created exclusively for subscribers and will not be reprinted in the same format. From custom dust jackets to bespoke interior design elements, each book is intended to feel like a permanent part of a collector’s shelf.
                </p> 
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="d-md-flex flex-md-row-reverse">
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 p-2">
                <img class="rounded-circle" src="/images/scifantasy.png">
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-8 p-2">
                <h2>Fantasy+Sci-Fi Subscription</h2>
                <p>
                    €240 per year
                    <br>
                    Fantasy and science fiction, curated together. 
                    <br>
                    The Speculative Fiction Combo Subscription combines the Fantasy and Science Fiction selections into a single, streamlined subscription. Titles alternate between genres, offering variety while maintaining the same production standards and exclusivity as the individual subscriptions. This option is ideal for readers who enjoy speculative fiction broadly and want comprehensive coverage without managing multiple subscriptions.
                </p> 
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row justify-content-center">
    <div class="col-md-10 col-lg-8 col-xl-6">
        <h3>Apple To Our Waiting List</h1>
        <p>We can only produce so many books at once without sacrificing quality and so our subscribptions have a limited amount of users. We are always expanding our capacity every chance we get so hopefully you won't be waiting long.</p>
        <form action="submission" name="commentForm" method="GET">
            <div class="mb-3">
                <label for="emailAddress" class="form-label">Your e-mail</label>
                <input type="email" class="form-control" id="userEmail" name="userEmail" placeholder="name@example.ie" required>
            </div>
            <div class="mb-3">
                <label for="comment" class="form-label">Your Desired Subscription</label>
                <select class="form-control" name="userComment" id="comment" required>
                  <option value="scifi">Sci-Fi</option>
                  <option value="fantasy">Fantasy</option>
                  <option value="scififantasy">Sci-Fi + Fantasy</option>
                </select>         
            </div>
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Submit</button>
        </form>
    </div>
    </div>

</main>